An integer c is a common divisor of two integers x and y if and only if c is a divisor of x and c is a divisor of y. Which of the following sets of integers could possibly be the set of all common divisors of two integers?____.
A. {-6,-2, -1, 1, 2, 6}
B. {-6, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2, 6}
C. {-6, -3, -2, -1, 1, 2, 3, 6}
D. {-6, -3, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2, 3, 6}

Any set of Boolean operators that is sufficient to represent all Boolean expressions is said to be complete. Which of the following is NOT complete?____.
A. {AND, NOT}
B. {NOT, OR}
C. {AND, OR}
D. {NAND}
